content:
Sure, here's an example of HTML and CSS code for a basic sidebar with navigation links:

HTML:

```
<div class="sidebar">
  <nav>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="#">Home</a></li>
      <li><a href="#">About</a></li>
      <li><a href="#">Contact</a></li>
    </ul>
  </nav>
</div>
```

CSS:

```
.sidebar {
  background-color: #f2f2f2;
  width: 200px;
  position: fixed;
  height: 100%;
  left: 0;
  top: 0;
  overflow-x: hidden;
  padding-top: 20px;
}

.sidebar a {
  padding: 8px 8px 8px 32px;
  text-decoration: none;
  font-size: 16px;
  color: #333;
  display: block;
  transition: 0.3s;
}

.sidebar a:hover {
  background-color: #ddd;
}

.sidebar li {
  margin: 0;
  padding: 0;
  list-style: none;
}
```

You can then position your other content alongside the sidebar with CSS, for example:

```
.main-content {
  margin-left: 220px;
  /* adjust the margin to fit your specific layout */
}
```
